  "time_ut": 1656565671,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0db8\u0dca\u0db6\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0ddc\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0daf\u0ddc\u0db9\u0d9a\u0dbb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hambantota Port Cranes to handle cement raw materials",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A pair of brand new Chinese-made cranes are being unloaded at Berth No. 6 of the Hambantota International Port (HIP) to transport bulk raw materials to the newly constructed cement plant, the port announced. The gantry cranes, fully assembled and transported by barges, arrived at HIP within 6 weeks from the port of Shenzhen, China.",
        "Cranes built to meet HIP regulations and environmental standards will be used to handle clinker, gypsum and slag raw materials. Cranes are used to transfer the raw materials from the ship to a de-dusting hopper and transport them directly through a conveyor belt to the factory located in Mirijjawila BOI zone, 2 km from the port.",
        "\"Navadombakara, the high operational efficiency of the vessels has a very positive effect on our productivity. The port started handling bulk cargo after the Hambantota International Port Group (HIPG) took over the operations in 2018. Since then, we have been able to break records in efficiency volumes, and this innovation has improved our operations. It will further improve and help to double the productivity levels,\" says Tissa Wickramasinghe, HIPG's Chief Operating Officer.",
        "The Hambantota International Port added that these cranes, which have the capacity to handle 600 tons of raw materials per hour with a lifting speed of 120 meters per minute, will help to carry out operations in a more environmentally friendly manner."
      ],
